00:29:51,100 --> 00:29:53,650
It never stops. You won't even
have time for your own family.

568
00:29:55,020 --> 00:29:55,689
I'm not saying

569
00:29:55,690 --> 00:29:57,409
other jobs are easy,

570
00:29:57,410 --> 00:29:58,929
but at least some careers

571
00:29:58,930 --> 00:30:00,690
are less demanding than being a doctor.

572
00:30:03,210 --> 00:30:04,320
I know, Mom.

573
00:30:22,970 --> 00:30:23,779
Huan'er.

574
00:30:23,780 --> 00:30:25,299
Do you feel any discomfort?

575
00:30:25,300 --> 00:30:26,450
I'm okay.

576
00:30:27,170 --> 00:30:28,410
Come eat.

577
00:30:29,740 --> 00:30:30,689
Mom.

578
00:30:30,690 --> 00:30:33,209
Where's my red and white towel?

579
00:30:33,210 --> 00:30:34,850
It's hanging on the balcony.

580
00:30:39,690 --> 00:30:41,320
Come eat.

581
00:30:41,690 --> 00:30:42,800
Okay.

582
00:30:50,450 --> 00:30:53,000
(You should rest well, Huan'er.)

583
00:30:53,340 --> 00:30:55,480
(You're incredible, Huan'er!)

584
00:30:55,780 --> 00:30:57,130
(Are you all right?)

585
00:30:57,340 --> 00:30:58,579
(We left the school clinic)

586
00:30:58,580 --> 00:31:01,169
(before checking if you were feeling all right.)

587
00:31:01,170 --> 00:31:02,410
(You should take medical leave.)

588
00:31:17,340 --> 00:31:18,410
Chen Huan'er.

589
00:31:32,540 --> 00:31:33,480
What's the matter?

590
00:31:33,580 --> 00:31:34,800
Are you feeling better now?

591
00:31:35,580 --> 00:31:36,960
I'm okay.

592
00:31:37,370 --> 00:31:38,130
I...

593
00:31:40,650 --> 00:31:43,320
My mom was just being overly protective.

594
00:31:45,020 --> 00:31:46,850
Rest early.

595
00:31:48,740 --> 00:31:49,650
Good night.

596
00:31:56,210 --> 00:31:57,689
Come eat, Huan'er.

597
00:31:57,690 --> 00:31:58,800
Coming.

598
00:32:10,410 --> 00:32:11,739
Chen Huan'er.

599
00:32:11,740 --> 00:32:13,610
Why can't she participate in Sports Day?

600
00:32:14,970 --> 00:32:16,410
She was sick when she was little.

601
00:32:16,610 --> 00:32:17,760
She has a weak constitution.

602
00:32:17,860 --> 00:32:19,450
We live in the same compound.

603
00:32:19,500 --> 00:32:21,720
You should look out for her.

604
00:32:28,020 --> 00:32:29,609
Don't tell my mom

605
00:32:29,610 --> 00:32:30,889
I joined Sports Day.

606
00:32:30,890 --> 00:32:32,369
Don't snitch on me.

607
00:32:32,370 --> 00:32:33,850
Why the secrecy?

608
00:32:37,890 --> 00:32:38,969
You had an IV drip?

609
00:32:38,970 --> 00:32:40,080
Did you faint?

610
00:32:40,080 --> 00:32:42,739
I told you not to join Sports Day.
You need to take care of yourself.

611
00:32:42,740 --> 00:32:44,320
Why won't you listen?

612
00:33:08,130 --> 00:33:08,960
Come on.

613
00:33:10,260 --> 00:33:11,130
Breakfast.

614
00:33:11,450 --> 00:33:12,280
Thanks.

615
00:33:12,450 --> 00:33:13,560
This candy is for you too.

616
00:33:13,860 --> 00:33:15,280
To prevent low blood sugar.

617
00:33:15,580 --> 00:33:17,090
You mustn't faint again.

618
00:33:30,375 --> 00:33:31,739
She's not a patient.

619
00:33:31,740 --> 00:33:33,210
What are you doing?

620
00:33:34,060 --> 00:33:35,059
That's right.

621
00:33:35,060 --> 00:33:37,000
I'm perfectly healthy now.

622
00:33:37,170 --> 00:33:37,859
Do you hear me?

623
00:33:37,860 --> 00:33:39,520
Stop treating her differently.

624
00:33:41,370 --> 00:33:42,819
By the way. We have a test today.

625
00:33:42,820 --> 00:33:43,969
We need to hurry.

626
00:33:43,970 --> 00:33:45,410
A test? Today?

627
00:33:46,210 --> 00:33:47,689
Mr. Xu mentioned it yesterday.

628
00:33:47,690 --> 00:33:49,019
The school is so cruel,

629
00:33:49,020 --> 00:33:51,370
giving us a test right after Sports Day.

630
00:33:52,370 --> 00:33:53,339
You really didn't

631
00:33:53,340 --> 00:33:54,650
listen to the teacher.

632
00:33:56,540 --> 00:33:59,280
(I was grateful for Jing Xichi.)

633
00:33:59,580 --> 00:34:01,339
(He eased my awkwardness)

634
00:34:01,340 --> 00:34:03,000
(with a joke.)

635
00:34:03,740 --> 00:34:05,760
(Perhaps he's right.)

636
00:34:06,370 --> 00:34:07,819
(I just want to be normal,)

637
00:34:07,820 --> 00:34:10,170
(like everyone else.)

638
00:34:10,300 --> 00:34:11,280
Chen Huan'er.

639
00:34:12,340 --> 00:34:13,280
Coming.

640
00:34:26,090 --> 00:34:26,880
Liang.

641
00:34:28,300 --> 00:34:30,690
- What is it?
- Are you watching the match?

642
00:34:33,220 --> 00:34:35,089
Didn't we make a bet

643
00:34:35,090 --> 00:34:37,280
before Sports Day?

644
00:34:43,570 --> 00:34:44,720
Chi.

645
00:34:45,090 --> 00:34:46,369
Stop it.

646
00:34:46,370 --> 00:34:48,050
I wasn't serious about that.

647
00:34:48,260 --> 00:34:49,089
Liang.

648
00:34:49,090 --> 00:34:50,970
Well, listen.

649
00:34:58,820 --> 00:34:59,650
Chi.

650
00:35:00,930 --> 00:35:01,760
Chi.

651
00:35:09,530 --> 00:35:11,369
This is about the Cultural Festival.

652
00:35:11,370 --> 00:35:13,819
There's going to be
a Bookcrossing Event.

653
00:35:13,820 --> 00:35:14,969
Go home

654
00:35:14,970 --> 00:35:17,010
and pick your favorite book.

655
00:35:17,370 --> 00:35:18,529
You can

656
00:35:18,530 --> 00:35:21,049
leave a message for the next student

657
00:35:21,050 --> 00:35:22,170
who gets your book.

658
00:35:22,220 --> 00:35:23,369
After you finish reading,

659
00:35:23,370 --> 00:35:25,320
remember to reply
to the message you receive too.

660
00:35:25,320 --> 00:35:28,200
The class monitor will collect the books
and send them to the Reading Room.

661
00:35:28,200 --> 00:35:31,569
Mr. Xu. Does that mean the class monitor
will know what books we get?

662
00:35:31,570 --> 00:35:34,050
Of course
she will pick her favorite one.

663
00:35:34,890 --> 00:35:36,690
Who do you like?

664
00:35:37,050 --> 00:35:38,920
I mean, she'll pick
the book that she likes.

665
00:35:38,930 --> 00:35:41,010
I'll throw yours in the bin first.

666
00:35:42,780 --> 00:35:43,920
Well, if that's the case,

667
00:35:44,010 --> 00:35:46,089
you can submit your book
directly to the Reading Room.

668
00:35:46,090 --> 00:35:49,320
We won't force you to join the free study
period on Friday afternoons.

669
00:35:49,410 --> 00:35:52,210
You'll have plenty of time to read.

670
00:35:54,370 --> 00:35:54,929
Alright.

671
00:35:54,930 --> 00:35:56,489
What nonsense.

672
00:35:56,490 --> 00:35:57,464
By the end of this month,

673
00:35:57,465 --> 00:35:59,815
you need to submit
an 800-word reflection on the book.

674
00:36:02,860 --> 00:36:03,369
All right.

675
00:36:03,370 --> 00:36:04,560
You can study on your own now.

676
00:36:07,620 --> 00:36:08,440
Huan'er.

677
00:36:08,820 --> 00:36:11,089
Do you want
to grab milk tea together after school?

678
00:36:11,090 --> 00:36:12,409
We can talk about book selection.

679
00:36:12,410 --> 00:36:13,760
Sure.

680
00:36:16,570 --> 00:36:17,920
Let's invite them too.

681
00:36:20,300 --> 00:36:23,440
Qi Qi is asking if you want
to get milk tea after school.

682
00:36:23,930 --> 00:36:24,859
Pure invitation.

683
00:36:24,860 --> 00:36:26,130
Are you treating us then?

684
00:36:26,140 --> 00:36:27,170
Bill's on me.

685
00:36:27,260 --> 00:36:28,739
I want to thank you

686
00:36:28,740 --> 00:36:30,090
for helping me with revision.

687
00:36:30,820 --> 00:36:31,880
A treat?

688
00:36:32,050 --> 00:36:33,210
Am I included?

689
00:36:33,660 --> 00:36:35,690
You always get excited
when someone treats.

690
00:36:36,570 --> 00:36:37,889
Yes, you can join.

691
00:36:37,890 --> 00:36:39,210
You're truly my friend.

692
00:36:44,170 --> 00:36:47,569
(Open)

693
00:36:47,570 --> 00:36:48,570
Song Cong.

694
00:36:48,620 --> 00:36:50,720
Have you thought
about what book to bring?

695
00:36:51,490 --> 00:36:52,139
Well.

696
00:36:52,140 --> 00:36:53,490
Not yet.

697
00:36:53,700 --> 00:36:56,050
What do you usually read?

698
00:36:56,890 --> 00:36:58,010
Normally,

699
00:36:58,220 --> 00:37:00,219
I don't have a particular preference.

700
00:37:00,220 --> 00:37:01,600
(Open)
I read all sorts of book.

701
00:37:04,740 --> 00:37:05,329
Qi Qi.

702
00:37:05,330 --> 00:37:06,409
(Open)

703
00:37:06,410 --> 00:37:08,454
What book did you choose?

704
00:37:08,455 --> 00:37:08,969
(Open)

705
00:37:08,970 --> 00:37:09,969
Don't tell me

706
00:37:09,970 --> 00:37:11,800
it's another melodramatic youth novel.

707
00:37:14,450 --> 00:37:15,840
That's none of your business.

708
00:37:15,840 --> 00:37:18,240
Besides, participation matters
more than the book itself.

709
00:37:18,240 --> 00:37:19,680
What if someone doesn't have any books?

710
00:37:19,930 --> 00:37:20,929
Don't drag me into this.

711
00:37:20,930 --> 00:37:22,320
I have books.

712
00:37:22,930 --> 00:37:23,859
What book?

713
00:37:23,860 --> 00:37:26,800
Even though I don't like studying,

714
00:37:27,090 --> 00:37:28,280
I actually

715
00:37:28,820 --> 00:37:30,490
enjoy reading.

716
00:37:31,970 --> 00:37:34,440
(Open)

717
00:37:35,860 --> 00:37:36,699
Come here, Huan'er.

718
00:37:36,700 --> 00:37:38,369
(Open)

719
00:37:38,370 --> 00:37:40,440
Come to my house later
and pick a book.

720
00:37:40,930 --> 00:37:42,090
Won't that trouble you?

721
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:43,179
No worries.

722
00:37:43,180 --> 00:37:43,970
Come on.

723
00:37:44,410 --> 00:37:45,490
- I'll take it.
- Come on.

724
00:37:46,050 --> 00:37:46,569
Goodbye.

725
00:37:46,570 --> 00:37:47,369
Bye!

726
00:37:47,370 --> 00:37:58,009
(Open)

727
00:37:58,010 --> 00:37:59,960
Since when did you
take an interest in reading?

728
00:38:07,300 --> 00:38:08,210
Come on in.

729
00:38:17,140 --> 00:38:18,760
Your house is huge!

730
00:38:26,260 --> 00:38:28,490
And your piano, it looks magnificent.

731
00:38:30,490 --> 00:38:31,970
This?

732
00:38:35,370 --> 00:38:37,610
My mom forced me to play the piano.

733
00:38:37,890 --> 00:38:40,170
I wanted to learn the ukulele,

734
00:38:40,820 --> 00:38:42,210
but she wouldn't allow it.

735
00:38:42,370 --> 00:38:44,130
She said it wasn't presentable.

736
00:38:45,620 --> 00:38:46,969
Ukulele?

737
00:38:46,970 --> 00:38:48,280
What's that?

738
00:38:48,570 --> 00:38:49,970
Why do you want to play the ukulele?

739
00:38:50,260 --> 00:38:51,760
A ukulele

740
00:38:51,890 --> 00:38:53,049
is a small musical instrument

741
00:38:53,050 --> 00:38:55,650
that you can carry anywhere.

742
00:38:55,740 --> 00:38:56,409
I

743
00:38:56,410 --> 00:38:58,970
wanted to play it because

744
00:39:00,010 --> 00:39:01,840
I dream of wandering the world with it.

745
00:39:03,180 --> 00:39:04,400
Wandering the world?

746
00:39:07,300 --> 00:39:09,089
You really dream big.

747
00:39:09,090 --> 00:39:10,739
If I had the chance,

748
00:39:10,740 --> 00:39:12,840
I'd love to travel the world too.

749
00:39:13,010 --> 00:39:14,090
Really?

750
00:39:14,410 --> 00:39:15,779
But for now,

751
00:39:15,780 --> 00:39:18,320
I want to focus on the present.

752
00:39:19,010 --> 00:39:20,280
You're back, Qi Qi.

753
00:39:20,820 --> 00:39:22,130
Greetings, Aunt.

754
00:39:23,260 --> 00:39:24,440
Have some fruits.

755
00:39:24,860 --> 00:39:25,449
Thank you.

756
00:39:25,450 --> 00:39:26,650
Thank you, Aunt.

757
00:39:29,090 --> 00:39:30,130
Qi Qi.

758
00:39:30,220 --> 00:39:32,130
Your mom is really kind.

759
00:39:35,090 --> 00:39:37,130
That's my housekeeper.

760
00:39:37,740 --> 00:39:38,969
If you met my mom,

761
00:39:38,970 --> 00:39:40,400
you wouldn't say that.

762
00:39:43,780 --> 00:39:45,050
Let's go pick a book.

763
00:39:49,180 --> 00:39:50,360
Take a look here.

764
00:39:52,010 --> 00:39:53,179
Qi Qi.

765
00:39:53,180 --> 00:39:55,320
You have so many books at home!

766
00:39:56,090 --> 00:39:57,360
Did you know?

767
00:39:57,410 --> 00:39:59,089
I used to love reading as a kid,

768
00:39:59,090 --> 00:40:00,409
mostly because

769
00:40:00,410 --> 00:40:02,440
I loved the smell of books.

770
00:40:05,260 --> 00:40:06,130
They smell great.

771
00:40:06,140 --> 00:40:06,969
Try it

772
00:40:06,970 --> 00:40:07,970
Really?

773
00:40:16,930 --> 00:40:18,130
I'm sorry.

774
00:40:18,300 --> 00:40:19,929
I have a nose allergy.

775
00:40:19,930 --> 00:40:20,699
It's okay.

776
00:40:20,700 --> 00:40:22,320
I'll take this.
Go ahead and pick a book.

777
00:40:26,010 --> 00:40:27,739
There are too many!

778
00:40:27,740 --> 00:40:30,010
I don't know which one to choose.

779
00:40:30,340 --> 00:40:31,210
Qi Qi.

780
00:40:31,220 --> 00:40:32,219
How about this?

781
00:40:32,220 --> 00:40:33,779
Just help me pick one book.

782
00:40:33,780 --> 00:40:35,090
That won't do.

783
00:40:35,450 --> 00:40:36,339
Your favorite book

784
00:40:36,340 --> 00:40:37,219
says

785
00:40:37,220 --> 00:40:38,889
a lot about you.

786
00:40:38,890 --> 00:40:40,699
The person who chooses your book

787
00:40:40,700 --> 00:40:42,089
likely shares

788
00:40:42,090 --> 00:40:43,970
the same taste.

789
00:40:44,090 --> 00:40:46,090
You might even be soul mates.

790
00:40:51,780 --> 00:40:52,720
Huan'er.

791
00:40:53,180 --> 00:40:56,440
Which books did
Song Cong and Jing Xichi pick?

792
00:40:56,450 --> 00:40:57,720
Tell me.

793
00:40:58,700 --> 00:41:00,720
I don't want to choose the same one.

794
00:41:00,930 --> 00:41:02,929
That's very unlikely.

795
00:41:02,930 --> 00:41:04,570
We've already picked our books...

796
00:41:05,620 --> 00:41:06,440
No.

797
00:41:07,260 --> 00:41:10,139
Song Cong might have that book at home.

798
00:41:10,140 --> 00:41:11,490
I'll ask them later.

799
00:41:58,620 --> 00:41:59,610
Qi Qi.

800
00:42:00,050 --> 00:42:01,690
You're right.

801
00:42:01,780 --> 00:42:03,739
I should pick a book

802
00:42:03,740 --> 00:42:04,889
from my own collection.

803
00:42:04,890 --> 00:42:05,619
That way,

804
00:42:05,620 --> 00:42:07,280
it truly represents me.

805
00:42:08,090 --> 00:42:08,920
Okay.

806
00:42:14,450 --> 00:42:15,570
Mom.

807
00:42:16,620 --> 00:42:18,650
Mom.

808
00:42:18,930 --> 00:42:20,320
Mom!

809
00:42:21,660 --> 00:42:24,009
My school is organizing
a Bookcrossing event.

810
00:42:24,010 --> 00:42:25,049
Do you have any books

811
00:42:25,050 --> 00:42:26,779
I can borrow?

812
00:42:26,780 --> 00:42:28,840
Why not take one of your own?

813
00:42:31,930 --> 00:42:33,320
Well, mine

814
00:42:33,450 --> 00:42:35,490
are too basic.

815
00:42:35,930 --> 00:42:36,409
Mom.

816
00:42:36,410 --> 00:42:37,489
Listen.

817
00:42:37,490 --> 00:42:39,659
I went to Qi Qi's place today.

818
00:42:39,660 --> 00:42:41,080
Her house is really massive.

819
00:42:41,080 --> 00:42:42,259
She has so many books.

820
00:42:42,260 --> 00:42:43,369
I couldn't even

821
00:42:43,370 --> 00:42:45,720
understand some of the titles.

822
00:42:45,740 --> 00:42:48,130
No wonder she's so good at writing.

823
00:42:48,620 --> 00:42:51,170
If I recommend one of my books,

824
00:42:52,090 --> 00:42:53,800
it'll seem

825
00:42:54,300 --> 00:42:55,369
boring in comparison.

826
00:42:55,370 --> 00:42:57,090
You want something interesting?

827
00:42:57,300 --> 00:42:57,726
Come on.

828
00:42:57,727 --> 00:42:59,009
Check my bookshelf.

829
00:42:59,010 --> 00:43:00,859
My books are interesting.

830
00:43:00,860 --> 00:43:02,480
(Goldman-Cecil Medicine)
It's surely interesting.

831
00:43:02,480 --> 00:43:04,720
Your classmates would be impressed.
Pick whichever you like.

832
00:43:04,720 --> 00:43:05,659
It's not impressing,

833
00:43:05,660 --> 00:43:08,089
it's depressing.

834
00:43:08,090 --> 00:43:10,139
(Dictionary of Traditional Chinese Medicine)

835
00:43:10,140 --> 00:43:11,369
How can I recommend this?

836
00:43:11,370 --> 00:43:12,529
Why not?

837
00:43:12,530 --> 00:43:14,179
It's Science.

838
00:43:14,180 --> 00:43:15,610
Look, this book is about gynecology.

839
00:43:16,090 --> 00:43:17,179
Girls like you

840
00:43:17,180 --> 00:43:18,529
should learn about it.

841
00:43:18,530 --> 00:43:19,929
If you ever have symptoms

842
00:43:19,930 --> 00:43:21,139
or anything...

843
00:43:21,140 --> 00:43:21,659
Mom.

844
00:43:21,660 --> 00:43:23,619
Enough with the medical jargon.

845
00:43:23,620 --> 00:43:24,299
I can't

846
00:43:24,300 --> 00:43:25,299
recommend this.

847
00:43:25,300 --> 00:43:27,049
Why can't you recommend these?

848
00:43:27,050 --> 00:43:28,720
It's about the human body.

849
00:43:30,370 --> 00:43:31,610
This one's on acupuncture.

850
00:43:32,050 --> 00:43:35,010
We're only in senior middle school,
we can't do acupuncture!

851
00:43:35,740 --> 00:43:36,720
Well.

852
00:43:38,740 --> 00:43:39,650
What about this?

853
00:43:40,500 --> 00:43:41,859
The Compendium of Materia Medica.

854
00:43:41,860 --> 00:43:43,760
A classic.

855
00:43:44,220 --> 00:43:46,610
Teach my classmates
about herbal medicine? Never mind.

856
00:43:47,410 --> 00:43:48,210
Mom.

857
00:43:48,820 --> 00:43:51,210
Don't you have any normal books?

858
00:43:51,220 --> 00:43:52,010
That's right.

859
00:43:52,090 --> 00:43:53,179
I've only read

860
00:43:53,180 --> 00:43:54,409
half of this one,

861
00:43:54,410 --> 00:43:55,650
but I can lend it to you.

862
00:43:58,570 --> 00:44:01,050
Neuropsychology.

863
00:44:01,700 --> 00:44:02,449
Or

864
00:44:02,450 --> 00:44:03,299
I have another one,

865
00:44:03,300 --> 00:44:04,259
abnormal psychology.

866
00:44:04,260 --> 00:44:05,659
It's even more compelling.
Where did I put it?

867
00:44:05,660 --> 00:44:07,130
Forget the abnormal one.

868
00:44:07,410 --> 00:44:08,650
I rather choose the neuro book.

869
00:44:09,820 --> 00:44:12,259
You sure you don't want something fresh?
My books are fresh.

870
00:44:12,260 --> 00:44:13,760
Trust me.

871
00:44:13,860 --> 00:44:15,440
I'll have a look.

872
00:44:57,800 --> 00:45:02,970
♪Fallen leaves flutter past your gaze♪

873
00:45:04,760 --> 00:45:09,840
♪I dream of worlds within your days♪

874
00:45:11,610 --> 00:45:16,960
♪Countless times,
I write your name in my heart♪

875
00:45:17,270 --> 00:45:22,760
♪Wishes whispered to the stars above♪

876
00:45:25,350 --> 00:45:30,370
♪How many faces in the glass I see♪

877
00:45:32,160 --> 00:45:37,400
♪Time's gentle hand
pulling me out of my cocoon♪

878
00:45:39,000 --> 00:45:44,420
♪Under the sun,
a rainbow butterfly takes flight♪

879
00:45:44,880 --> 00:45:50,380
♪To rest upon your left shoulder bright♪

880
00:45:51,580 --> 00:45:55,540
♪I still hear your promise in my ears♪

881
00:45:55,540 --> 00:46:00,530
♪Before we said goodbye,
your spirit free♪

882
00:46:00,660 --> 00:46:04,090
♪And full of life♪

883
00:46:05,380 --> 00:46:08,840
♪If summer could last a little longer♪

884
00:46:08,840 --> 00:46:13,950
♪Would regrets rewrite
where we'd gone wrong?♪

885
00:46:14,210 --> 00:46:18,600
♪And let me be there with you
at the end of the story♪

886
00:46:19,100 --> 00:46:23,000
♪Watching your silhouette from behind♪

887
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:27,940
♪My footsteps slow, we were too young♪

888
00:46:27,940 --> 00:46:30,730
♪To know right from wrong♪

889
00:46:32,640 --> 00:46:36,170
♪Your sweat-kissed face
I hold in my memory♪

890
00:46:36,170 --> 00:46:39,420
♪Glows as bright as ever♪

891
00:46:39,580 --> 00:46:45,340
♪I hope one day we'll meet again♪

892
00:46:45,760 --> 00:46:50,360
♪At just the right time♪
